HEADWORD: Antemural
<hw>An`te*mu"ral</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>antemurale</ets>: <ets>ante</ets> + <ets>murus</ets> wall. See
<er>Mural</er>.]</ety> <def>An outwork of a strong, high wall, with
turrets, in front of the gateway (as of an old castle), for defending
the entrance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antenatal</ent>⟦br⟧
